  "prompt": "Can one change branch from biotechnology engineering to engineering physics in IIT Roorkee?",
  "response": "Changing branches in IIT Roorkee, including from Biotechnology to Engineering Physics, is possible, but it's highly competitive and depends on several factors:\n\n**Key Factors Determining Eligibility:**\n\n*   **Academic Performance (CGPA/CPI):** This is the *most important* factor.  IIT Roorkee, like most IITs, has a minimum CGPA requirement for branch changes. This cutoff usually hovers between 8.0 to 9.0, and it can change depending on the overall performance of the batch.  **Your CGPA needs to be significantly higher than the minimum cutoff to have a good chance.**\n*   **Availability of Seats:**  There must be vacancies in the Engineering Physics branch.  These vacancies arise from students leaving the department (e.g., dropping out, switching branches themselves).  Naturally, more vacancies mean better chances for everyone.\n*   **Specific Rules and Regulations:**  IIT Roorkee has specific rules governing branch changes. These rules may include restrictions on which branches can be changed into which others.  **You *must* carefully read the institute's branch change policy document for the relevant academic year.** This document will clearly state the eligibility criteria, the application process, and any branch-specific restrictions.\n\n**General Process and Considerations:**\n\n1.  **Check the Institute's Branch Change Policy:** This policy is usually published online (on the IIT Roorkee website) before the application period. It will contain all the essential information. *This is your first step.*\n2.  **Maintain a High CGPA:** Focus on doing very well in your first-year courses. Your first-year CGPA will be the primary factor in determining your eligibility.\n3.  **Application:**  There will be a formal application process, usually online.  You'll need to fill out a form and submit it by the deadline.\n4.  **Merit-Based Selection:** The branch change is almost entirely merit-based.  The higher your CGPA, the better your chances.\n5.  **Consider the Course Content:** Engineering Physics and Biotechnology Engineering are quite different. Before applying, make sure you understand the curriculum and career prospects of Engineering Physics and are genuinely interested in it. Speak to current Engineering Physics students to get their perspectives.\n\n**Likelihood of Success:**\n\n*   **Competitive:** Branch changes in IITs are generally very competitive. Engineering Physics is a popular choice for students seeking a more fundamental, mathematically-oriented engineering discipline. This competition drives the cutoff CGPA even higher.\n*   **Depends on Vacancies and CGPA:** The availability of seats in Engineering Physics will influence your chances. Also, a high CGPA is a must.\n*   **Biotechnology to Engineering Physics is a Common Direction:** Students sometimes change from fields such as Biotechnology to more core engineering fields if they find their interests are more aligned with physics, math and coding.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\nChanging from Biotechnology Engineering to Engineering Physics at IIT Roorkee is *possible*, but it's **extremely competitive and heavily reliant on your CGPA and the availability of seats.**  Carefully review the institute's branch change policy, strive for an excellent CGPA in your first year, and make sure you genuinely want to switch to Engineering Physics.  Speak with students and faculty in both departments to make an informed decision. Don't rely on rumors or anecdotes; check the official IIT Roorkee website for the most accurate and up-to-date information.\n",
